comment: The function ` S ` , that maps a closed subspace to the square of the norm of its projection onto a unit vector, is a Jauch-Piron state. Remark in [Mayet] p. 370. (See ~ strlem3a for the proof that ` S ` is a state.) (Contributed by NM, 8-Apr-2001.) (New usage is discouraged.)
